    • Method Detail

      • cast

        public static <E,S extends com.google.common.collect.ImmutableCollection<? extends E>,T extends com.google.common.collect.ImmutableCollection<E>> T cast(S collection)
        Safely upcasts the element type of an immutable collection. This operation is safe thanks to the input being immutable. This can help adapt instances of immutable collection to otherwise invariant collection types, without the need for unchecked casts.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the element type of the collection
        S - the source type of the collection being re-cast
        T - the target type to which the collection is re-cast
        Parameters:
        collection - an immutable collection
        Returns:
        the input collection, but with its element type re-cast

      • cast

        public static <K,V,S extends com.google.common.collect.ImmutableMap<? extends K,? extends V>,T extends com.google.common.collect.ImmutableMap<K,V>> T cast(S map)
        Safely upcasts the key and/or value types of an immutable map. This operation is safe thanks to the input being immutable. This can help adapt instances of immutable map to otherwise invariant map types, without the need for unchecked casts.
        Type Parameters:
        K - the key type of the map
        V - the value type of the map
        S - the source type of the map being re-cast
        T - the target type to which the map is re-cast
        Parameters:
        map - an immutable map
        Returns:
        the input map, but with its key or value type (or both) re-cast
